definition: warm/lukewarm/temperature/to warm up/mild/soft/tender/to review (a lesson etc)/fever (TCM)/old variant of 瘟[wen1]
Slovakia/Slovak/abbr. for 斯洛伐克[Si1 luo4 fa2 ke4]
to stop/to pause/to arrange/to lay out/to kowtow/to stamp (one's foot)/at once/classifier for meals, beatings, scoldings etc: time, bout, spell, meal

sentences.english: Yeah, Barney, Winston tastes good like a cigarette should.
sentences.chinese: 是的，巴尼，温斯顿吸起来才是真正的香烟。

sentences.english: He immediately brought winston back into the government as minister of munitions .
sentences.chinese: 他很快让温斯顿回到政府，成为军需品大臣。

sentences.english: Winston had recovered part of his self-possession.
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿已恢复了他的一部分自信。

sentences.english: Winston, if I were your wife I'd put poison in your coffee.
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿，如果我是你老婆，就会在你咖啡里下毒。

sentences.english: Winston's entrails seemed to have turned into ice.
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿的五脏六腑似乎都变成了冰块。

sentences.english: The regimental mascot is a goat called winston.
sentences.chinese: 该团的吉祥物是一只名叫温斯顿的山羊。

sentences.english: He looked up, and his spectacles darted a hostile flash in Winston's direction.
sentences.chinese: 他抬起头来，眼镜朝温斯顿方向闪了一下敌意的光。

sentences.english: 4 lookings at the outside of the gauze curtain absentmindedly .
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿心不在焉地看着薄纱窗帘的外面。

sentences.english: If you are a man, Winston, you are the last man .
sentences.chinese: 如果你是人，温斯顿，那你就是最后一个人了。

sentences.english: When your taste grows up, Winston out-tastes them all.
sentences.chinese: 当你的鉴赏力提高以后，你会发现温斯顿味道最佳。

sentences.english: Why can't I combine that with Stan Winston's doing?
sentences.chinese: 为什么我不能将它与斯坦温斯顿的技术结合起来呢？

sentences.english: Winston looked at the thing sulkily and without interest.
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿不高兴地看一眼，毫无兴趣。

sentences.english: She revived, turned to have another look at Winston.
sentences.chinese: 她恢复了精神，转过身来又看一眼温斯顿。

sentences.english: Winston’s now husband packed an ice chest full of fast food.
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿现在的丈夫准备了装满快餐的冰盒。

sentences.english: Winston let out the water and disgustedly removed the clot of human hair that had blocked up the pipe.
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿放掉污水，强忍恶心掏出堵塞水管的一团毛发。

sentences.english: Winston, if I were your wife I’d put poison in your coffee.
sentences.chinese: 温斯顿，如果我是你老婆，就会在你咖啡里下毒。

definition: Wellington, capital of New Zealand (Tw)/Wellington (name)/Arthur Wellesley, Duke of Wellington (1769-1851)
